WEBVTT

00:00:00.510 --> 00:00:03.600
I promise I'll catch the culprit.

00:00:03.600 --> 00:00:04.780
You must reboot.

00:00:04.780 --> 00:00:07.210
I can turn you into Gido.

00:00:07.210 --> 00:00:08.990
How much is in here?

00:00:08.990 --> 00:00:11.200
I'd estimate about ten billion yen.

00:00:11.200 --> 00:00:15.310
He must really play the part
if you haven't caught on yet.

00:00:15.310 --> 00:00:18.630
A real shame that Riku Hayase has to go.

00:00:18.630 --> 00:00:20.980
I will ask you one last time.

00:00:20.980 --> 00:00:23.900
Where did you put the ten billion yen?

00:00:23.900 --> 00:00:25.990
I'm not Gido!

00:00:25.990 --> 00:00:27.970
The real deal stole the money.

00:00:27.970 --> 00:00:31.330
Three years ago, Gido stole the billion,

00:00:31.330 --> 00:00:34.370
murdered Natsumi-san, and then buried her.

00:00:34.370 --> 00:00:35.970
Gido was behind it all?

00:00:35.970 --> 00:00:41.340
Gido was on the verge of arrest,
with the Inspector General hot on his tail.

00:00:41.340 --> 00:00:45.610
At his wits' end,
Gido came to me with a proposal.

00:00:45.610 --> 00:00:50.070
I'm rebooting. Pull a fast one on me,

00:00:50.070 --> 00:00:52.310
and your sister's dead.

00:00:52.310 --> 00:00:55.160
His plan was to pressure Riku Hayase-san
into a corner

00:00:55.160 --> 00:00:58.660
and have him reboot as "Gido."

00:00:58.660 --> 00:01:01.410
Sounds utterly unbelievable.

00:01:01.410 --> 00:01:03.920
Allow me to prove myself.

00:01:05.100 --> 00:01:08.570
I will bring you the real Gido.

00:01:08.570 --> 00:01:12.980
[Ayumi Gido, Reboot, Day 5]

00:01:17.960 --> 00:01:19.430
Fried rice, at this hour?

00:01:19.430 --> 00:01:21.080
To lift our spirits.

00:01:21.080 --> 00:01:24.430
Can't fight on an empty stomach, right?

00:01:25.490 --> 00:01:27.280
Thank you.

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:29.170
Of course.

00:01:32.580 --> 00:01:35.760
- It's delicious.
- Hot.

00:01:41.940 --> 00:01:46.450
I forgot how hungry I was.

00:01:49.930 --> 00:01:51.700
Only 23 hours left.

00:01:51.700 --> 00:01:54.250
We have to find Gido.

00:01:55.050 --> 00:01:57.880
What will you do once you've cornered Gido?

00:01:58.980 --> 00:02:01.900
I won't hand him to Goroku.

00:02:01.900 --> 00:02:07.280
I'll have him confess everything to the police.

00:02:07.280 --> 00:02:10.710
That way, I will be proven innocent.

00:02:12.660 --> 00:02:14.650
It won't be so easy.

00:02:14.650 --> 00:02:17.470
You must be referring to Goroku's spy
within the force.

00:02:17.470 --> 00:02:19.150
Yes.

00:02:19.150 --> 00:02:21.450
Besides, even if you are proven innocent,

00:02:21.450 --> 00:02:25.000
Goroku won't allow you to roam free.

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:26.820
I know.

00:02:26.820 --> 00:02:30.040
That's why I'll end Goroku's
organization while I'm at it.

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:32.300
How?

00:02:32.300 --> 00:02:36.560
I'll tell the police all I know
about his money laundering.

00:02:36.560 --> 00:02:40.590
One of our teams already has eyes on him.

00:02:40.590 --> 00:02:45.380
We believe GooSix's CEO
is using Fuyuhashi's group

00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:50.940
to organize an extensive
money laundering scheme.

00:02:50.940 --> 00:02:55.810
Once they know how the money flows,
they will arrest Goroku.

00:02:57.540 --> 00:03:01.790
But I will need your assistance.

00:03:02.960 --> 00:03:06.230
Could you send me the data you have?

00:03:09.650 --> 00:03:14.840
If Goroku is put under scrutiny,
I'll also be caught.

00:03:17.740 --> 00:03:21.870
I understand I must atone,

00:03:21.870 --> 00:03:26.410
but I want to save my sister
before I'm arrested.

00:03:30.730 --> 00:03:35.580
The stolen ten billion is not yet liquidated.

00:03:35.580 --> 00:03:37.810
Once Gido is arrested,

00:03:37.810 --> 00:03:40.120
take your share of the riches

00:03:40.120 --> 00:03:43.350
- and fly off to the States.
- What?

00:03:43.350 --> 00:03:47.100
No one would catch on immediately.

00:03:47.100 --> 00:03:49.730
Let your sister be treated

00:03:49.730 --> 00:03:54.570
while the police are looking into the case.

00:03:54.570 --> 00:03:57.490
I promise not to speak a word of this.

00:03:57.490 --> 00:04:03.190
In exchange, once your sister has recovered,

00:04:03.190 --> 00:04:05.670
I ask that you turn yourself in.

00:04:10.190 --> 00:04:11.830
Okay.

00:04:13.870 --> 00:04:17.970
But first, we have to find Gido
before the organization does.

00:04:17.970 --> 00:04:20.010
What do you mean?

00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:22.760
Ten billion yen in luxury items were stolen.

00:04:22.760 --> 00:04:25.890
Goroku will divert all his resources

00:04:25.890 --> 00:04:29.060
to hunting down Gido.

00:04:29.060 --> 00:04:33.020
He may even resort to using Mayu-san as bait.

00:04:33.020 --> 00:04:35.980
I thought he avoided roping in third parties.

00:04:35.980 --> 00:04:38.710
The amount stolen means risks are necessary.

00:04:38.710 --> 00:04:41.360
Goroku is prepared to take extreme measures.

00:04:43.960 --> 00:04:47.490
We can't let Mayu-san get involved in this mess.

00:04:47.490 --> 00:04:49.310
Worry about yourself first.

00:04:49.310 --> 00:04:50.820
I know.

00:04:50.820 --> 00:04:53.120
We only have 23 hours.

00:04:53.120 --> 00:04:56.960
If we can't manage to find Gido,
we won't live to see tomorrow.

00:04:57.630 --> 00:05:00.290
So we'll find him.

00:05:00.290 --> 00:05:07.970
Timing and subtitles by
"🍰 The Pastry Detectives 🔍" Team @Viki.com

00:05:07.970 --> 00:05:10.920
Let's come up with a code.

00:05:10.920 --> 00:05:12.320
A code?

00:05:12.320 --> 00:05:15.450
Gido might try to trick me again.

00:05:19.650 --> 00:05:21.510
Then how about this?

00:05:22.470 --> 00:05:25.520
When I see you, I'll grab my ears.

00:05:25.520 --> 00:05:28.890
It's something my mother used to do to me.

00:05:28.890 --> 00:05:31.940
Natsumi and I did the same to Takumi as well.

00:05:32.880 --> 00:05:34.270
Sure, that works.

00:05:34.270 --> 00:05:35.790
Great.

00:05:36.770 --> 00:05:38.930
One more thing.

00:05:38.930 --> 00:05:43.420
Gido threatened you to reboot me, right?

00:05:43.420 --> 00:05:47.490
Do you know where he was
in the six months I spent recovering?

00:05:47.490 --> 00:05:49.340
I don't know.

00:05:50.110 --> 00:05:54.120
I was only told to call in
every now and then.

00:05:57.040 --> 00:05:59.150
I'll try calling this number.

00:06:06.180 --> 00:06:10.220
The number you have called is unavailable

00:06:10.220 --> 00:06:12.040
or no longer in use.

00:06:12.040 --> 00:06:13.900
He's not answering.

00:06:13.900 --> 00:06:16.450
Is it possible he's already left the country?

00:06:16.450 --> 00:06:20.950
With how much he stole,
he wouldn't be able to leave immediately.

00:06:37.340 --> 00:06:38.790
You called me here bright and early

00:06:38.790 --> 00:06:44.010
to use the facial recognition system?

00:06:44.010 --> 00:06:46.380
Please don't call me when I'm off duty, Sir.

00:06:46.380 --> 00:06:50.010
I wanted to look up Riku Hayase again.

00:06:50.010 --> 00:06:52.680
Adachi, do I drag the photo here?

00:06:52.680 --> 00:06:55.820
Yes, Sir. Then you click this button here.

00:07:01.910 --> 00:07:04.700
We haven't managed to get a hit thus far.

00:07:04.700 --> 00:07:09.110
Our system only receives a feed
from cameras in public facilities.

00:07:09.110 --> 00:07:11.300
Though this helps identify individuals,

00:07:11.300 --> 00:07:14.410
it's not the best resource
for tracking someone down.

00:07:19.120 --> 00:07:27.640
[Ayumi Gido]

00:07:27.640 --> 00:07:29.880
There are only pictures of me.

00:07:34.070 --> 00:07:35.980
I’m going to the Hayase Patisserie.

00:07:35.980 --> 00:07:39.190
Sir, we looked into Ichika Kogo like you asked.

00:07:39.190 --> 00:07:40.350
According to GooSix Corp...

00:07:40.350 --> 00:07:42.260
You can drop that lead.

00:07:45.740 --> 00:07:48.000
He visits that patisserie every day.

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:51.520
Mr. Gido sure likes to act solo
ever since his return.

00:07:51.520 --> 00:07:55.990
You make a point.

00:07:55.990 --> 00:07:57.300
Hey there, you two.

00:07:57.300 --> 00:07:58.950
Chief Mikami. Good morning, Sir.

00:07:58.950 --> 00:08:02.070
I'd like to introduce you two to someone.

00:08:02.070 --> 00:08:05.550
What a quaint office.

00:08:07.330 --> 00:08:09.200
[GooSix Co. Business Plan]

00:08:09.200 --> 00:08:11.460
Sir, it seems they're informed.

00:08:11.460 --> 00:08:14.710
Great. Then this will be quick.

00:08:14.710 --> 00:08:17.650
Excuse me, those are important documents.

00:08:17.650 --> 00:08:19.270
It's fine, let them.

00:08:19.270 --> 00:08:20.870
And you are?

00:08:20.870 --> 00:08:24.330
This is Inspector General Makita.

00:08:25.400 --> 00:08:28.190
Hey, no need to get so stiff.

00:08:28.190 --> 00:08:31.150
We've come to ask for your assistance
in an investigation.

00:08:31.150 --> 00:08:33.200
An investigation?

00:08:33.200 --> 00:08:37.530
We have reason to believe Inspector Gido
has a hand in dishonorable work.

00:08:38.690 --> 00:08:43.200
Please tell us everything you know of him.

00:08:43.200 --> 00:08:46.330
It would be in your best interests
to cooperate.

00:08:53.500 --> 00:08:55.200
I'm heading out.

00:08:55.200 --> 00:08:57.970
Taku-chan, your gym clothes.

00:08:57.970 --> 00:08:59.660
Thanks.

00:08:59.660 --> 00:09:02.870
I'll help with the caramel when I get back.
Don't push yourself, okay?

00:09:02.870 --> 00:09:05.810
Thank you, Dear. Go ahead now.

00:09:05.810 --> 00:09:06.910
- Be careful.
- Okay.

00:09:06.910 --> 00:09:08.850
Have a good one, kid.

00:09:21.820 --> 00:09:23.850
Takumi-kun seemed to be in high spirits.

00:09:23.850 --> 00:09:29.640
He's only acting that way to ease my worries.

00:09:29.640 --> 00:09:35.630
School can't be any easier,
with all the rumors about his father.

00:09:36.800 --> 00:09:39.420
You have a wonderful grandson.

00:09:50.970 --> 00:09:52.390
Are you all right?

00:09:52.390 --> 00:09:54.650
I'm fine.

00:09:54.650 --> 00:09:57.870
Please, rest. I'll finish up what remains.

00:09:57.870 --> 00:10:00.070
It's fine, I have to protect the store.

00:10:00.070 --> 00:10:04.990
Ma'am, my husband will find the culprit
and bring your son home.

00:10:04.990 --> 00:10:09.800
So please, rest when you can,
for his beloved store's sake.

00:10:12.630 --> 00:10:15.070
Thank you.

00:10:15.820 --> 00:10:18.170
Then I'll be in the back.

00:10:27.260 --> 00:10:29.580
Welcome.

00:10:34.430 --> 00:10:36.650
Sorry, it's me.

00:10:41.650 --> 00:10:45.350
Mayu-san, has Gido contacted you?

00:10:45.350 --> 00:10:47.070
No.

00:10:47.070 --> 00:10:49.330
If he does, please tell me immediately.

00:10:49.330 --> 00:10:54.070
I'd advise you to lay low as well.

00:10:54.070 --> 00:10:56.800
Did something happen to Gido?

00:10:59.680 --> 00:11:01.430
I can't tell you the specifics.

00:11:01.430 --> 00:11:05.400
It would only put you in more danger.

00:11:06.550 --> 00:11:11.590
I also ask that you leave this store.

00:11:13.140 --> 00:11:16.850
While I truly appreciate all your help,

00:11:16.850 --> 00:11:20.010
I want to keep my family out of this mess.

00:11:22.670 --> 00:11:24.440
I understand.

00:11:24.440 --> 00:11:27.840
But before I go, please share with us
your pudding recipe.

00:11:27.840 --> 00:11:33.070
Your mother and Takumi-kun are working hard
to recreate the Hayase Pudding.

00:11:33.070 --> 00:11:37.110
It's the caramel that's giving them trouble.

00:11:44.930 --> 00:11:48.900
Mayu-chan, please leave this store while you can.

00:11:48.900 --> 00:11:50.980
Did you look into Ichika-san?

00:11:50.980 --> 00:11:54.550
Yes. I've resolved the issue already.

00:11:54.550 --> 00:11:57.590
Please, be wary of her.

00:11:57.590 --> 00:11:59.070
I believe she's lying to you.

00:11:59.070 --> 00:12:02.960
That's the very issue I've resolved.

00:12:02.960 --> 00:12:06.130
Ichika-san is someone I can trust.

00:12:08.040 --> 00:12:10.780
Please heed my advice.

00:12:19.600 --> 00:12:23.530
Morning, Gido-san.

00:12:23.530 --> 00:12:28.370
Kiriya wasn't informed of my identity.

00:12:28.370 --> 00:12:31.550
What brings you here, Kiriya?

00:12:31.550 --> 00:12:35.580
We're tailing that woman. Fuyuhashi-san's orders.

00:12:35.580 --> 00:12:37.520
One more thing, he said.

00:12:38.500 --> 00:12:43.210
"Kidnap him if he tries to run."

00:12:53.070 --> 00:12:55.640
Gido's here with me.

00:13:02.650 --> 00:13:04.440
Fuyuhashi.

00:13:04.440 --> 00:13:09.430
Pop quiz. What did you make for us last night?

00:13:11.960 --> 00:13:14.350
A Hayase Shortcake.

00:13:14.350 --> 00:13:16.050
Hand the phone back.

00:13:19.060 --> 00:13:21.410
Hello?

00:13:22.240 --> 00:13:24.680
Sure thing.

00:13:31.400 --> 00:13:33.230
He says you're free to go.

00:13:33.230 --> 00:13:37.560
I'm guessing you screwed up, right?

00:13:38.240 --> 00:13:42.570
My advice? Never disobey Goroku-san.

00:13:42.570 --> 00:13:44.210
See you around.

00:14:08.940 --> 00:14:12.740
- Yes?
- Mayu-san, about the caramel.

00:14:12.740 --> 00:14:15.340
It's a bit on the bitter side now.

00:14:15.340 --> 00:14:19.600
Add water as soon as the sugar bubbles.

00:14:19.600 --> 00:14:22.450
If you mess up that timing, it turns bitter.

00:14:23.200 --> 00:14:25.780
Okay, we'll give it a try.

00:14:25.780 --> 00:14:28.970
I'll come to taste test again tomorrow.

00:14:28.970 --> 00:14:30.430
Sounds good.

00:14:31.340 --> 00:14:33.020
[Transplant Surgical Costs]

00:14:33.020 --> 00:14:37.400
At the current exchange rate,
her surgery would cost about 210 million yen.

00:14:37.400 --> 00:14:40.960
Her primary doctors
would also accompany her to the U.S.

00:14:40.960 --> 00:14:42.530
Though it depends on her condition,

00:14:42.530 --> 00:14:46.880
she will likely be procedure-ready
in about a week.

00:14:46.880 --> 00:14:49.190
I understand.

00:14:50.890 --> 00:14:55.140
I will have the money.
Please prepare her for the operation.

00:15:09.960 --> 00:15:11.820
Hey there.

00:15:11.820 --> 00:15:15.290
What's up? I already had breakfast.

00:15:15.290 --> 00:15:17.820
I was talking to your doctor.

00:15:17.820 --> 00:15:21.120
We're getting you to the U.S. for a transplant.

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:22.670
But what about the money?

00:15:22.670 --> 00:15:24.970
Money is no issue.

00:15:24.970 --> 00:15:27.770
I've saved up plenty.

00:15:28.840 --> 00:15:30.610
You're headed over soon.

00:15:30.610 --> 00:15:33.400
Prepare yourself, okay?

00:15:36.950 --> 00:15:38.970
I have to get going.

00:15:38.970 --> 00:15:42.680
Why do you earn so much more now?

00:15:42.680 --> 00:15:44.460
Simple. I work hard.

00:15:45.620 --> 00:15:48.660
Just don't work too hard, okay?

00:15:48.660 --> 00:15:51.630
I want you to prioritize yourself.

00:15:51.630 --> 00:15:54.220
You think I don't do that already?

00:15:54.220 --> 00:15:55.900
See you around.

00:16:11.090 --> 00:16:12.830
Our code.

00:16:17.710 --> 00:16:19.980
Where are we?

00:16:19.980 --> 00:16:23.470
Fuyuhashi and Machi run an NPO together

00:16:23.470 --> 00:16:27.440
to provide shelter for homeless children.

00:16:27.440 --> 00:16:29.340
And this, is that very "Shelter."
[Shelter]

00:16:29.340 --> 00:16:31.700
The one Natsumi helped establish?

00:16:31.700 --> 00:16:32.990
That's right.

00:16:32.990 --> 00:16:36.720
She found this building for them.

00:16:36.720 --> 00:16:40.400
Say what you will, but this is all a front

00:16:40.400 --> 00:16:43.550
for hiring more shady part-timers, right?

00:16:44.330 --> 00:16:49.630
All right everyone, lunch is served.

00:16:49.630 --> 00:16:52.150
Eat up while it's hot.

00:16:54.130 --> 00:16:57.830
Don't hesitate to ask for seconds.

00:16:57.830 --> 00:17:01.120
Hey, what's with the lukewarm reaction?

00:17:01.120 --> 00:17:04.070
Here, have some pork miso soup, Yukie.

00:17:04.070 --> 00:17:05.550
Miso soup with pasta?

00:17:05.550 --> 00:17:08.270
Sorry, Fuyuhashi was craving miso.

00:17:08.270 --> 00:17:09.560
- What sort of pairing is that?
- Right?

00:17:09.560 --> 00:17:13.030
I promise they taste great together.

00:17:13.030 --> 00:17:15.520
Go on, dig in.

00:17:26.840 --> 00:17:28.760
- See, they're great together!
- No, they're not.

00:17:28.760 --> 00:17:33.620
- It's delicious!
- The kids at Shelter know nothing of crime.

00:17:33.620 --> 00:17:36.100
Sure, the place is run by dirty money.

00:17:36.100 --> 00:17:40.120
But the kids are innocent.

00:17:40.120 --> 00:17:42.300
- Could we get another bowl?
- Coming right up!

00:17:42.300 --> 00:17:45.870
I never knew Fuyuhashi
could look so cheerful.

00:17:45.870 --> 00:17:46.970
Here you go.

00:17:46.970 --> 00:17:50.730
Fuyuhashi used to volunteer
on the city streets.

00:17:50.730 --> 00:17:53.950
That's where he met Machi-chan and his crew.

00:17:53.950 --> 00:17:57.550
Their goal was to start an NPO together.

00:17:57.550 --> 00:18:02.030
He wanted to create a sanctuary
for kids who had no home.

00:18:07.830 --> 00:18:09.020
But

00:18:09.020 --> 00:18:14.750
a scuffle with some child traffickers
left him fatally injured.

00:18:16.770 --> 00:18:19.920
You must be Fuyuhashi-kun.

00:18:19.920 --> 00:18:23.040
The one who saved him, was Goroku.

00:18:24.370 --> 00:18:27.310
You certainly have grand ambitions.

00:18:28.760 --> 00:18:31.040
But those ambitions won't bear fruit.

00:18:32.160 --> 00:18:34.480
Do you know why?

00:18:36.890 --> 00:18:41.970
It's because you're a child,
who knows nothing of the world.

00:18:44.140 --> 00:18:47.410
Come join me, and I will teach you.

00:18:47.410 --> 00:18:51.990
About money, power,
and how to correctly wield them both.

00:18:56.660 --> 00:19:02.340
I have a large family.

00:19:05.060 --> 00:19:07.830
Can they come with me?

00:19:07.830 --> 00:19:10.050
Of course. I welcome them all.

00:19:34.670 --> 00:19:38.430
What now? Aren't you two busy chasing Gido?

00:19:38.430 --> 00:19:41.740
Aren't you going to join your lackeys
in the search?

00:19:42.560 --> 00:19:45.320
We've come to ask for intel.

00:19:45.320 --> 00:19:47.950
Gido most likely hopes to leave the country.

00:19:47.950 --> 00:19:50.400
But we're in possession of his passport.

00:19:50.400 --> 00:19:54.840
We expect he'll take the back route out.
Has your group...

00:19:54.840 --> 00:19:58.450
We've already asked around
all sorts of channels.

00:19:58.450 --> 00:20:01.510
He hasn't gotten himself caught yet.

00:20:01.510 --> 00:20:04.010
If that's all, then leave us.

00:20:05.420 --> 00:20:08.120
Please don't bring Mayu-san into this.

00:20:09.320 --> 00:20:12.890
She knows nothing of this seedy business.

00:20:13.810 --> 00:20:16.260
She's plenty involved already as Gido's wife.

00:20:16.260 --> 00:20:19.310
Gido was hoping to divorce Mayu-san.

00:20:19.310 --> 00:20:21.930
I cannot imagine he'd escape with her.

00:20:21.930 --> 00:20:23.960
She was his family, at one point.

00:20:23.960 --> 00:20:28.100
Kidnap her, and we could lure him out.

00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:37.970
Why are you doing all this?

00:20:38.920 --> 00:20:43.020
I understand you wish to help these kids.

00:20:44.220 --> 00:20:47.120
Yet you kill without blinking an eye.

00:20:48.540 --> 00:20:51.160
Why do you follow Goroku's orders?

00:20:57.180 --> 00:20:59.510
For money, why else?

00:21:02.080 --> 00:21:06.520
Goroku and I are the only ones
who know of your identity.

00:21:06.520 --> 00:21:11.620
Now keep up the Gido act, yeah?

00:21:11.620 --> 00:21:13.720
Fine.

00:21:17.720 --> 00:21:19.920
We have to hurry, or else Mayu-san is in danger.

00:21:19.920 --> 00:21:21.670
I know.

00:21:21.670 --> 00:21:24.970
Do you have any idea where she may be now?

00:21:26.150 --> 00:21:28.520
She's currently helping out the store.

00:21:28.520 --> 00:21:30.610
What? Why?

00:21:30.610 --> 00:21:33.130
She insisted.

00:21:33.130 --> 00:21:35.040
You have to get her out of there.

00:21:35.040 --> 00:21:36.670
I know.

00:21:39.440 --> 00:21:41.190
Wait.

00:21:42.490 --> 00:21:44.750
[Do your best at work]
[Secret meeting with your boyfriend]

00:21:46.550 --> 00:21:49.520
- Gido.
- We're heading to the hospital first.

00:21:55.470 --> 00:21:57.330
You suck at this.

00:21:57.330 --> 00:22:00.640
My bad, Ichika-chan always did the cooking.

00:22:00.640 --> 00:22:03.390
Good going, you lovebirds.

00:22:14.830 --> 00:22:17.010
There can't be two of you.

00:22:17.010 --> 00:22:19.940
I can't send you there alone.

00:22:19.940 --> 00:22:22.000
I'll keep you on the line.

00:22:23.200 --> 00:22:25.600
Say the word, and I'll come running.

00:22:53.840 --> 00:22:56.510
You're here again.

00:22:58.200 --> 00:22:59.340
Where's Gido?

00:22:59.340 --> 00:23:01.290
He already left.

00:23:01.290 --> 00:23:03.750
I see.

00:23:03.750 --> 00:23:05.660
So why did you come?

00:23:06.490 --> 00:23:09.610
Did you come for Gido-san?

00:23:09.610 --> 00:23:11.770
Let me guess. You two fought?

00:23:11.770 --> 00:23:14.310
No. I just wanted to see you again.

00:23:14.310 --> 00:23:17.090
Yikes.

00:23:22.490 --> 00:23:24.000
Was he there?

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:26.190
No, he left.

00:23:33.950 --> 00:23:35.780
What's our code?

00:23:39.710 --> 00:23:41.490
Where's Hayase-san?

00:23:41.490 --> 00:23:42.570
What do you mean?

00:23:42.570 --> 00:23:45.340
Answer me, now.

00:23:46.270 --> 00:23:49.130
He's in the car.

00:23:49.130 --> 00:23:51.220
I haven't killed him.

00:24:02.200 --> 00:24:04.540
Let him go.

00:24:04.540 --> 00:24:08.200
Not until you apologize.

00:24:10.770 --> 00:24:12.880
Traitor.

00:24:15.060 --> 00:24:19.260
Bring me the money.
Or else your sister's dead.

00:24:19.260 --> 00:24:21.280
Hayase-sasn has nothing to do with this.

00:24:21.280 --> 00:24:23.780
You sure get heated when it comes to him.

00:24:23.780 --> 00:24:27.790
What? Did you fall for him or something?

00:24:30.350 --> 00:24:33.130
You have until tonight.

00:25:12.580 --> 00:25:15.730
We sure do look alike, don't we?

00:25:20.290 --> 00:25:23.440
Quit acting so tough, Pâtissier.

00:25:24.310 --> 00:25:27.320
You murdered Natsumi, didn't you?

00:25:28.910 --> 00:25:31.350
Answer me.

00:25:31.350 --> 00:25:35.300
You sure are naive.

00:25:35.300 --> 00:25:38.020
Take a look at your surroundings.

00:25:39.260 --> 00:25:41.880
Screaming won't do you any good.

00:25:41.880 --> 00:25:45.230
What's in it for me if I answer?

00:25:50.390 --> 00:25:55.080
Stand in my shoes for a second.

00:25:55.850 --> 00:25:58.060
A dunce is parading around with my face.

00:25:58.060 --> 00:26:02.180
Can you blame me for being pissed off?

00:26:03.100 --> 00:26:06.720
You've got a brain in there so use it.

00:26:06.720 --> 00:26:08.480
What got you into this mess?

00:26:08.480 --> 00:26:11.770
Why are you tied up?

00:26:11.770 --> 00:26:14.930
Deceive me like your life depends on it.

00:26:14.930 --> 00:26:18.100
Bargain with me like we're equals.

00:26:18.100 --> 00:26:21.640
Guess that's not possible for an idiot

00:26:21.640 --> 00:26:27.030
who lets his emotions dictate him, huh?

00:26:30.920 --> 00:26:35.650
You're a naive,
sweets-making goody-two-shoes.

00:26:35.650 --> 00:26:39.390
It's no wonder you couldn't save Natsumi.

00:26:49.780 --> 00:26:52.710
Kiriya is tailing Mayu-san.

00:26:56.750 --> 00:27:02.020
Fuyuhashi plans to use Mayu-san to drag you out.

00:27:03.290 --> 00:27:06.680
I don't care about that woman.

00:27:06.680 --> 00:27:08.380
Liar.

00:27:10.100 --> 00:27:12.910
I saw the photo in your locker.

00:27:14.380 --> 00:27:18.220
You still treasure Mayu-san.

00:27:18.220 --> 00:27:22.790
It's why you distanced yourself from her.

00:27:23.530 --> 00:27:25.550
You're acting delusional.

00:27:25.550 --> 00:27:28.870
Mayu-san loves you, even now.

00:27:30.460 --> 00:27:33.240
She worries for you, day and night.

00:27:33.240 --> 00:27:35.630
She misses you.

00:27:38.630 --> 00:27:41.460
I can save her.

00:27:43.200 --> 00:27:48.510
And that's supposed to be a negotiation?

00:27:49.370 --> 00:27:51.670
So what? Do I just trust you'll keep your word?

00:27:51.670 --> 00:27:53.840
I will.

00:27:53.840 --> 00:27:57.990
Because I'm a naive, goody-two-shoes.

00:27:59.880 --> 00:28:01.680
Mayu-san is a wonderful individual.

00:28:01.680 --> 00:28:04.850
I don't want to get her involved, either.

00:28:05.860 --> 00:28:10.950
You wouldn't leave an innocent soul to die,
would you?

00:28:18.140 --> 00:28:21.230
What'll you do once you rescue Mayu?

00:28:21.230 --> 00:28:24.730
What about your revenge against me?

00:28:24.730 --> 00:28:26.970
I'll have you turn yourself in.

00:28:29.420 --> 00:28:32.810
The man who murdered your wife is right here,

00:28:32.810 --> 00:28:36.980
and you'd let him get arrested,
without doing a thing yourself?

00:28:36.980 --> 00:28:38.970
You're a real softie, huh?

00:28:38.970 --> 00:28:42.300
If I had no one else in my life,
I'd kill you where you stand.

00:28:44.230 --> 00:28:46.550
But I can't do that.

00:28:48.170 --> 00:28:51.310
I promised my son I'd return to him.

00:28:52.180 --> 00:28:54.190
I promised Natsumi

00:28:54.950 --> 00:28:58.920
I'd make our child happy.

00:29:00.580 --> 00:29:05.550
It doesn't matter what troubles
or humiliations I must face.

00:29:05.550 --> 00:29:09.100
I vowed to return home to my family.

00:29:16.620 --> 00:29:22.200
I'm only alive
because you still think I have my uses, no?

00:29:25.720 --> 00:29:28.770
I can save Mayu-san.

00:29:28.770 --> 00:29:31.960
Please, hurry. We don't have much time.

00:29:38.720 --> 00:29:42.350
Seems like you've got a backbone, after all.

00:29:42.350 --> 00:29:44.590
Listen up.

00:29:46.100 --> 00:29:49.290
There's been a big misunderstanding here.

00:29:51.980 --> 00:29:55.100
I didn't kill Natsumi.

00:29:57.930 --> 00:30:00.520
Like hell I'd believe that.

00:30:00.520 --> 00:30:03.080
How would you explain the contents
of your warehouse?

00:30:03.080 --> 00:30:04.910
Warehouse?

00:30:04.910 --> 00:30:07.370
We looked through your laptop.

00:30:07.370 --> 00:30:09.110
[Warehouse Rental]

00:30:09.110 --> 00:30:12.910
We found the money
and Natsumi's belongings in your safe.

00:30:12.910 --> 00:30:17.990
Hold on. Where did you find that laptop?

00:30:17.990 --> 00:30:20.140
In your locker at the office.

00:30:21.750 --> 00:30:24.580
I think I'm catching on.

00:30:24.580 --> 00:30:29.040
She wants me to be guilty so bad, right?

00:30:31.490 --> 00:30:35.060
Ichika Kogo's playing you for a fool.

00:30:36.410 --> 00:30:37.470
Lies.

00:30:37.470 --> 00:30:40.670
Ichika's the liar.

00:30:40.670 --> 00:30:44.950
You threatened Natsumi
to help embezzle the organization's money.

00:30:45.650 --> 00:30:48.100
With the billion yen in your clutches,

00:30:48.100 --> 00:30:50.190
you murdered Natsumi
and pushed the blame onto me.

00:30:50.190 --> 00:30:55.450
It's true I threatened Natsumi
to help embezzle some cash.

00:30:55.450 --> 00:30:58.650
I was after the billion with Kaieda as well.

00:30:59.410 --> 00:31:02.230
But the money disappeared
before we could get our hands on it.

00:31:02.230 --> 00:31:04.920
I also didn't kill Natsumi.

00:31:06.290 --> 00:31:08.270
Then how do you explain the warehouse?

00:31:08.270 --> 00:31:11.840
I've never rented a warehouse in my name.

00:31:12.660 --> 00:31:16.250
The email you saw was a trap.

00:31:16.250 --> 00:31:18.410
A trap?

00:31:18.410 --> 00:31:21.980
Goroku's got another lackey in the police.

00:31:23.070 --> 00:31:24.140
Who?

00:31:24.140 --> 00:31:26.050
I don't know.

00:31:26.050 --> 00:31:28.920
But they're the ones who set up that laptop.

00:31:28.920 --> 00:31:32.570
Are you saying Goroku is behind all this?
I'd never believe it.

00:31:32.570 --> 00:31:35.170
Of course not.

00:31:35.170 --> 00:31:40.440
Why would Goroku steal money
left to his own organization?

00:31:41.170 --> 00:31:43.640
Goroku's already busy

00:31:43.640 --> 00:31:49.300
repaying the billion he lost.

00:31:49.300 --> 00:31:53.420
He can't stand to lose any more face.

00:31:53.420 --> 00:31:55.460
Then who's behind all this?

00:31:58.760 --> 00:32:02.670
Who checked the email?

00:32:05.440 --> 00:32:07.630
Ichika, right?

00:32:08.900 --> 00:32:12.340
Are you saying Ichika-san's the mastermind?

00:32:12.340 --> 00:32:16.980
Ichika's trying to use you
to make me the culprit.

00:32:17.910 --> 00:32:20.290
No.

00:32:20.290 --> 00:32:23.710
You threatened Ichika-san to have me rebooted.

00:32:23.710 --> 00:32:26.430
You're the one playing tricks on me.

00:32:26.430 --> 00:32:30.090
She's got you wrapped around her finger.

00:32:33.170 --> 00:32:37.750
Ichika's the one who suggested we reboot you.

00:32:42.130 --> 00:32:48.490
She brought it up when Natsumi was found,
and Goroku was on my back.

00:32:48.490 --> 00:32:51.790
If you're so backed into a corner,

00:32:51.790 --> 00:32:55.890
why don't we reboot someone
to take your place?

00:32:55.890 --> 00:32:58.300
Who the hell would take my place?

00:32:58.300 --> 00:33:02.450
Natsumi-san's husband, Riku Hayase.

00:33:03.890 --> 00:33:06.750
Place the blame on him,

00:33:06.750 --> 00:33:10.500
and he'll bite.

00:33:10.500 --> 00:33:12.980
I'll even give him the push he needs.

00:33:15.040 --> 00:33:17.140
I assumed she was eager to help

00:33:17.140 --> 00:33:21.660
to keep her own embezzling under wraps.

00:33:21.660 --> 00:33:26.410
But that wasn't her only goal.

00:33:26.410 --> 00:33:28.710
Once Hayase has been rebooted,

00:33:28.710 --> 00:33:33.050
escape overseas with the money.

00:33:33.050 --> 00:33:38.060
We'll simply place the blame on this fake.

00:33:39.850 --> 00:33:45.720
I only ask that I get 25% of the cut.

00:33:45.720 --> 00:33:48.730
Hey, I'm the one taking a risk here.

00:33:48.730 --> 00:33:51.600
Then I'll just have you killed.

00:33:51.600 --> 00:33:54.020
Does that work for you?

00:33:57.510 --> 00:34:00.940
I should've realized it was a faulty plan.

00:34:00.940 --> 00:34:02.880
Nothing was guaranteed,

00:34:02.880 --> 00:34:05.710
and I couldn't trust Ichika, either.

00:34:05.710 --> 00:34:09.900
But it was better than waiting for death.

00:34:09.900 --> 00:34:11.670
I've had it.

00:34:11.670 --> 00:34:13.100
I'm rebooting.

00:34:13.100 --> 00:34:14.890
- Sir.
- Hey.

00:34:14.890 --> 00:34:20.080
I exchanged Natsumi's laptop
for the one Ichika prepared for me

00:34:20.080 --> 00:34:23.120
and suspicion against you grew.

00:34:23.120 --> 00:34:26.510
The blood I added to you car
was the decisive blow.

00:34:26.510 --> 00:34:30.730
We're here to arrest Riku Hayase.

00:34:32.890 --> 00:34:36.330
All that was left
was for Ichika to convince you

00:34:37.190 --> 00:34:40.580
and for me to fake my own death.

00:34:54.160 --> 00:34:57.230
In the half year you spent recovering,

00:34:57.230 --> 00:35:00.720
I survived off whatever funds Ichika sent me,

00:35:00.720 --> 00:35:03.790
but I couldn't trust her for a second.

00:35:03.790 --> 00:35:07.330
I've been secretly observing
both your actions.

00:35:08.610 --> 00:35:11.140
I was supposed to steal the riches

00:35:11.140 --> 00:35:16.220
before you recovered.

00:35:16.220 --> 00:35:19.390
Then you'd waltz out, fully recovered,

00:35:19.390 --> 00:35:25.100
and get snuffed out. End of story.

00:35:26.400 --> 00:35:31.170
Except, that woman never reported back to me

00:35:31.170 --> 00:35:33.640
when you had made your recovery.

00:35:33.640 --> 00:35:38.220
If you ever need anything, come talk to me.

00:35:41.030 --> 00:35:44.440
I realized Ichika had played me like a fool.

00:35:45.600 --> 00:35:49.480
She even got Mayu involved in our mess.

00:35:52.970 --> 00:35:54.380
Yes?

00:35:54.380 --> 00:35:58.210
Keep walking, and don't turn left.

00:35:59.200 --> 00:36:00.410
Ayumi?

00:36:00.410 --> 00:36:02.810
Head into a crowded store.

00:36:02.810 --> 00:36:05.100
You're being followed.

00:36:07.170 --> 00:36:09.760
That's when I decided I'd trick her...

00:36:09.760 --> 00:36:11.480
He must really play the part.

00:36:11.480 --> 00:36:15.180
And make way with the riches myself.

00:36:16.310 --> 00:36:21.790
But even then, Ichika was a step ahead.

00:36:29.390 --> 00:36:32.400
All the jewels are fake.

00:36:32.400 --> 00:36:36.210
- The other riches? Complete junk.
- What?

00:36:36.210 --> 00:36:40.200
Ichika's the thief. I'm being framed.

00:36:40.200 --> 00:36:43.310
And both you and Goroku are convinced.

00:36:43.310 --> 00:36:46.960
Everything is going just as she planned.

00:36:48.370 --> 00:36:54.430
If I'm killed, the riches will remain missing.

00:36:54.430 --> 00:36:58.040
She'll get away with all the money.

00:36:58.960 --> 00:37:00.040
No...

00:37:00.040 --> 00:37:02.200
Think about it.

00:37:02.200 --> 00:37:05.740
The fact I'm still here
is proof enough, right?

00:37:06.990 --> 00:37:10.700
Why would I bother with Ichika
if I had all the money?

00:37:10.700 --> 00:37:13.760
Why would I detain you here?

00:37:15.630 --> 00:37:21.890
I suspect Ichika murdered Natsumi, too.

00:37:24.790 --> 00:37:26.940
Ichika-san had no ties
to the organization back then.

00:37:26.940 --> 00:37:32.320
Yes, that's also what I assumed.

00:37:32.320 --> 00:37:34.190
Turns out at the time,

00:37:34.190 --> 00:37:40.280
Ichika worked the night shift
at a club Goroku ran.

00:37:40.280 --> 00:37:42.510
That's where she met Natsumi,

00:37:42.510 --> 00:37:47.470
had her steal the billion,
and then killed her.

00:37:48.270 --> 00:37:50.810
It's not the craziest story, right?

00:37:53.200 --> 00:37:57.610
And now that Ichika's taken Natsumi's place,

00:37:57.610 --> 00:38:01.620
she's tricked us into getting her ten billion.

00:38:03.400 --> 00:38:07.180
- Unbelievable.
- I know, I'm right there with you.

00:38:07.180 --> 00:38:11.580
If I'm on the mark,
this is one terrifying woman we're dealing with.

00:38:11.580 --> 00:38:15.080
Ichika's goal isn't to save her sister.

00:38:15.080 --> 00:38:18.040
She's after something on a far greater scale.

00:38:26.060 --> 00:38:28.610
Ichika's calling.

00:38:38.730 --> 00:38:42.140
Is he the real, or fake? Guess.

00:38:42.140 --> 00:38:47.220
Hey. You better have
the ten billion ready for me.

00:38:48.710 --> 00:38:50.510
Mayu-san!

00:38:51.630 --> 00:38:53.150
I only put her to sleep,

00:38:53.150 --> 00:38:55.360
but she'll stay asleep until tomorrow.

00:38:55.360 --> 00:39:00.770
If you want to save her,
bring Riku Hayase to the location I specify.

00:39:00.770 --> 00:39:02.810
You have until 10 p.m.

00:39:28.730 --> 00:39:30.500
Do you have a gun?

00:39:30.500 --> 00:39:31.930
What?

00:39:31.930 --> 00:39:35.510
I'm asking if you have a working gun.

00:39:36.590 --> 00:39:38.520
There's one at your place.

00:39:39.970 --> 00:39:42.160
I'll come with you.

00:39:45.750 --> 00:39:48.490
You'll only be killed if you go alone.

00:39:49.330 --> 00:39:53.990
I will attempt to negotiate.
You're free to use brute force if I fail.

00:39:55.390 --> 00:39:57.370
Think rationally.

00:39:57.370 --> 00:40:01.670
We're more likely to save Mayu-san together.

00:40:03.490 --> 00:40:06.390
How do I know you won't betray me?

00:40:06.390 --> 00:40:09.350
I am a naive pâtissier.

00:40:10.490 --> 00:40:14.090
I cannot stand by
and watch an innocent person die.

00:40:50.520 --> 00:40:53.110
You piece of...

00:40:53.110 --> 00:40:57.750
You threatened Natsumi.
Let me have this much.

00:40:57.750 --> 00:41:03.150
Never underestimate a pâtissier.

00:41:30.300 --> 00:41:35.830
♫ It's wise not to expect anything ♫

00:41:38.630 --> 00:41:42.690
Does Mayu...

00:41:42.690 --> 00:41:44.590
She knows I'm not you.

00:41:49.510 --> 00:41:53.260
Listen, if I die...

00:41:53.960 --> 00:41:57.670
tell her I ran off with another woman.

00:41:59.340 --> 00:42:02.040
Tell her that yourself.

00:42:03.270 --> 00:42:05.980
And when you do, give her this.

00:42:10.710 --> 00:42:13.280
[Divorce papers]

00:42:15.210 --> 00:42:17.940
Give her this yourself.

00:42:17.940 --> 00:42:19.890
I'm counting on you.

00:42:32.580 --> 00:42:33.860
I'll head on in.

00:42:33.860 --> 00:42:35.660
Hurry.

00:43:22.280 --> 00:43:27.830
I'll have you know, we have a search warrant.

00:43:28.570 --> 00:43:32.800
- What brought this on?
- We're investigating Goroku's organization.

00:43:32.800 --> 00:43:36.360
We have reports of you with Fuyuhashi.

00:43:36.360 --> 00:43:37.930
I'm using him as an informant.

00:43:37.930 --> 00:43:39.490
But that's not all.

00:43:39.490 --> 00:43:42.630
Goroku's exclusive attorney
was a man named Kaieda.

00:43:42.630 --> 00:43:44.660
You know him, yes?

00:43:44.660 --> 00:43:48.520
We're told you were heard arguing with him.

00:43:48.520 --> 00:43:53.540
You only ran out after Fuyuhashi called, no?

00:43:55.170 --> 00:43:56.610
Adachi...

00:43:56.610 --> 00:43:59.600
I'm sorry for ratting you out, Sir.

00:44:00.690 --> 00:44:05.550
But this is for justice.

00:44:06.440 --> 00:44:09.130
You're cornered now.

00:44:09.130 --> 00:44:12.850
We'll hear more from you at the office.

00:44:14.460 --> 00:44:16.400
Please, wait.

00:44:16.400 --> 00:44:18.590
Can't this wait until tomorrow?

00:44:19.780 --> 00:44:22.590
Inspector General Makita, please.

00:44:24.890 --> 00:44:26.580
Take him.

00:44:26.580 --> 00:44:28.810
Sir.

00:44:28.810 --> 00:44:30.970
General Inspector, please.

00:45:20.860 --> 00:45:30.840
Timing and subtitles by
"🍰 The Pastry Detectives 🔍" Team @Viki.com

00:45:30.840 --> 00:45:36.630
[Reboot]

00:45:36.630 --> 00:45:39.560
This is where my reboot truly begins.
[Next, the last episode: Finale]

00:45:39.560 --> 00:45:42.100
Everything you've said is a lie.

00:45:42.100 --> 00:45:44.130
I expect great things from you, Gido.

00:45:44.130 --> 00:45:45.780
Goroku-san, please.

00:45:45.780 --> 00:45:47.380
Don't bring your issues into the home.

00:45:47.380 --> 00:45:49.460
Is Gido alive?
[Risking your life to protect your loved one]

00:45:49.460 --> 00:45:51.590
I will crush Ichika Kogo.
[Where will justice lead when the evil prevails..]

00:45:51.590 --> 00:45:53.300
I'll kill you. I mean it.

00:45:53.300 --> 00:45:55.110
Fuyuhashi, stop!

00:45:55.110 --> 00:45:56.750
Please, let Mayu-san go.

00:45:56.750 --> 00:46:00.430
Thought I'd prove what justice is all about.
[This drama is a work of fiction]